    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. i'm also looking at the ingredients and it lists a lot of different meat by-products and liver. is that actually okay for an older dog or should i be looking for something more \"pure\"?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Meat by-products and liver are often included in food to provide concentrated nutrients, like vitamins and minerals, which can be beneficial for older dogs. However, using too many processed by-products can sometimes lead to lower-quality ingredients or potential fillers. Look for brands that list recognizable, high-quality whole meat sources as the primary ingredients. If you are concerned, ask your vet to review the ingredient list for you.",
      "source": "target",
